---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/Hero.astro';
import FooterCta from '../../components/FooterCta.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Relationship Work — Arianna Buratti, Psychologist"
  description="Relationship-focused therapy with Arianna Buratti in Carlton, Melbourne. Helping individuals understand and improve their relationship patterns and build healthier connections."
  activeNav="services"
>

  <Hero
    title="Relationship Work"
    subtitle="Understanding your patterns and building healthier connections."
    image="/images/service-relationships.jpg"
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-section" style="max-width: 800px;">
      <h2>Your Relationships Start With You</h2>
      <hr class="divider" />
      <p>The quality of our relationships has a profound impact on our mental health and overall wellbeing. Relationship work in therapy isn't just for couples — it's for anyone who wants to understand their relational patterns and build more fulfilling connections.</p>
      <p>I work with individuals to explore:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Recurring patterns in relationships</li>
        <li>Attachment styles and how they affect your connections</li>
        <li>Communication difficulties</li>
        <li>Conflict resolution and boundary setting</li>
        <li>Recovery from relationship breakdowns or betrayal</li>
        <li>Co-dependency and people-pleasing behaviours</li>
        <li>Family-of-origin dynamics and their lasting effects</li>
        <li>Loneliness and social isolation</li>
        <li>Navigating separation or divorce</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--warm">
    <div class="container content-section" style="max-width: 800px;">
      <h2>How I Approach Relationship Work</h2>
      <hr class="divider" />
      <p>Using a combination of <a href="/approaches/">evidence-based approaches</a> — particularly Schema Therapy, Interpersonal Therapy (IPT), and ACT — we'll work together to identify the underlying patterns driving your relationship challenges.</p>
      <p>Therapy provides a safe space to examine how past experiences shape your current relationships, develop new skills for communication and emotional regulation, and build the confidence to create the connections you want in your life.</p>
      <p>Sessions are available in person at the Carlton practice or via <a href="/telehealth/">telehealth</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FooterCta title="Ready to Start?" body="Reach out to book your first session or ask any questions." />

</BaseLayout>
